        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=8359&TOPIC_ID=1238&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Spell+Book+Organization&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I personally have all the spells I currently use or might use on 16.5 pages.  All the old spells are on pages 35+.  I set my spell book up like this.  pages 1-2 all my lich, fear skulls spells.  I use them the most.  pages 3-4 personal buffs, pets 49-60, pet buff and heal spell.  Then pages 5-6 are my snares, undead spells, funky red hand icon buffs and my roots I think. The rest are just set up by icons to make it easier. I have all my chars set up the same way, by icons and by importance.  I used to have them set up by how I memmed them.  Pages 1-2 the spells I always use, snare, fear, pet, the dot I was currently using but that got old.  Now I pretty much know what page my spells types are on so I can do a /book 8 and know my gate spell is there.  </P><P>Hope this helps.  I have found it very useful.</P><P><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~molzdavis/lilsig.jpg"><br><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=33717">Guild Magic</A> and <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40671">Magelo</A><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
