        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> The /book command is your friend.</P><P>I have all my spells on one hotkey bank arranged thusly:</P><P>1)Gems (Book 1) all the spells that I need to toss up on the gem bar in an instant. Darkness, dots, fear, root, deflux, FD.</P><P>2)Bones. All my pets + pet buffs and Lich.</P><P>3)Buffs. Self buffs on one side, group buffs/mob debuffs on the other.</P><P>4)Invis.</P><P>5)Gate.</P><P>6)To Other. Heals, mana transfer spells.</P><P>7)Undead. Undead spells.</P><P>8)Dots. Misc dots and damage spells.</P><P>As a side note, my CoS stays in the same inventory slot, and every one of my spell banks gets a hotkey for it in the same slot, so no matter what hotkey bank I'm on, I've always got ready access to my wonderful little CoS.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32441">Sylphe  L'Cattivo</A><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
